caption: Tried one starter and Naan with paneer. May have better options to try.
The place offers a large variety of delicious food. I enjoyed eating here. The employees are always welcoming, pricing is fair and the spot is always neat.
This spot is good! Convenient prices, large portions and the staff are consistently super friendly.
I constantly arrive grabbing some food in this place. I enjoyed the efficient customer service and well made food. Never disappointing.
This place provides first-rate service as well as tasty menu. My favourite restaurant in the area. The food and drinks came out rapidly and the prices were inexpensive. Highly recommended.

I like this place! They serve high class meals, they have a rich menu, The chief cook in that place is a real authority in the kitchen, I enjoy very much tasting all their food. The food is consistently fresh and tasty, the service towards the visitors  is helpful. I frequently visit this place and I was never unsatisfied. I recommend it to all.
Good lunch Manu, it's open

Luxurious ambiance and decor. Authentic, delicious food. However, their quantity is so small and their prices are sky rocketing! If they want to stay, they have to reduce the price to make it reasonable as there is many more less expensive options for Indian cuisine in Bethesda. My recommendations for Passage to India is the black daal, kabobs, and butter chicken.
Foods are so expensive. Although the place was nice.
My favorite indian food place in Montgomery County.
I prefer this restaurant very much. It has a unique ambiance. The cuisine is good. the service is effective and the personel is polite. The cost is modest. I warmly recommend.
Nice restaurant . Good service. Tasty dishes!
I had a superb time at this place. We enjoyed the fantastic environment and the food. The staff members were very friendly. I’m glad we ultimately decided to visit this restaurant.
Tried this spot already with my friend and I am hooked ever since. I love the awesome mood and tasty dishes and drinks. 5 stars from me.
Dinner for 4 outside, undercover and the food was fabulous. We all enjoyed our dinner and the service was great.
Worth the Money, the Quality of the food, ambience and the service. Totally Loved it.

Authentic Indian food and pleasant ambiance. Menu is thoughtfully curated with very flavorful recipes from different parts of India.  Coorgi murgh (chicken in coconut milk), methi murgh (chicken in fenugreek curry) palkachi takatli bhaaji (spinach-buttermilk), baingan mirchi salan (eggplant-chilli), Amma’s pacha kari and kesar rasmalai are all delicious.
Average tasting Indian food. Service was good but there was no dish we had that stuck out to me.
Tasty Indian Food
Awesome and tasty food, I like the atmosphere the spot has, and the workers were kind. Will definitely visit here next time.
Best Indian Restaurant!

The ambiance is nice. The food is delicious. The decor of the restaurant is really nice, and it almost makes you feel like you went to a small museum with all the paintings and other artworks. The staff is also very nice. Overall, it’s a great place.
Excellent food at a decent price, great service and great quantity. I like to come here often and I would totally recommend it as an Indian restaurant.

I go to this superb place every couple of days because I like the  special atmosphere that is part of this place. The personel is exceptionally friendly and skilfull. The service is deeply rapid. Most important, the food you eat is perfect. I came often and I was never disappointed. The price is decent. I recommend this place to my friends and family.

First time ordering from Passage to India. I wanted something with a little kick to go with some Riesling I opened last night, and was super excited to see that they had goat curry. Said curry arrived promptly on time from GrubHub, and wow! It is really, really good. Beautiful spice aromas, lots of meat, just the right amount of heat. This exceeded my expecations and I will definitely be ordering from here again.
Very delicious and heart warming. Beautiful atmosphere, delectable food, and friendly staff. A bit on the pricier side, but average for Bethesda.
The food is so delicious that we were speechless!

I'd give more stars if I could. The fine people at Passage to India are some of the friendliest you'll find in the DMV area, and the food they prepare is second to none. They've reopened after a short COVID closure so we placed an order and the food is so good, I had to waddle over to the computer to leave a review. Thanks so much for top notch attitudes and service!
The food is regularly well prepared and flavorful, workers provides great service. I love how clean it is and ambience. I highly recommend this spot.

I had a unique dinning experience last night at passage to India restaurant. I was literally taken on a trip to East India. I recommend if you have a taste for authentic Indian cuisine Good Service ✅ Very Courteous and Friendly Staff ✅ ♿️Wheelchair Accessible Entrance ✅ 🚻Restroom✅
The food is amazing here. They have dishes from northern, southern, eatern and western India.

Customer service was very poor. Even if the food was good I wouldn't go back. I dont understand why they couldn't replace my side order of rice with bread. I placed the order of califlower with chickpeas and as a result my meal tasted mediocre. For someone who has high expectations this place didnt and will not make my list.
Great flavors and kind service
The service is consistently efficient, excellent vibes, super friendly employees. I will eat here again when I arrive in the area.

I admire this spot! They offer superb dishes, their menu is varied, The chief cook in that spot is well trained, I like very much eating all their dishes. The food is consistently fresh and tasty, the attitude towards the customers  is friendly. I frequently visit this place and I not even once was discontended. I recommend it to all my friends.
Refined decor. Beautiful designed menu which offers meals from different regions of India and different variations of spicy dishes. We all enjoyed our selection including the wines. Service was good.

This nicely decorated restaurant is conveniently located across from a Montgomery  County parking garage.  While we enjoyed our food, one of us had gastrointestinal distress after eating a fish dish.  What would be helpful on the server's part is to listen fully before offering menu guidance.  Not doing so led to unsolicited information, not helping us make a decision on entree.
Great decor, tasty fresh-tasting food. Attentive service. Quiet ambience. A bit pricey but worth it.
Very nice food from different regions of India and excellent service at a fair price - we really enjoyed it!
Great food and great service!
We.love the food- the make my husband's favorite chicken korma!
I always stop by grabbing some food in here. I enjoy the prompt customer service and well prepared dishes. Keep it up.
Lunch special (lamb) Quick service
Great food very accommodating when asked for something unusual . To then I can add Thank you . Excellent service!
Lovely dining room.  Interesting menu.  Kind staff.

We happened to order a takeout for Dal Makhani (Mah ki daal) with one Naan and one whole wheat Indian bread (tandoori roti). When we opened stuff to eat at home, we found out: 1. The “Tandoori Roti” looked ABSOLUTELY horrible. It’s color was so weird that I had never seen before in my entire life. The Naan was clearly not freshly made but taken out of a pack they sell in stores. 2. Dal Makhani (Mah Ki Daal): first of all, the lentils were not fully cooked and second it had no flavor. They have made a mockery of daal makhani! This was the first ever Indian food I have ever had from anywhere in the US. 👎

Service was poor. Servers were rude and discourteous and were not pleased with our order. We felt quite uncomfortable and unwelcome. We were not treated with the respect we had expected from the Passage to India. We went with high hopes and expectations but were disappointed.
Great food in a prime location.

I went there yesterday(6-15-19) and felt that I was being rushed through my dinner when I came to have a nice relaxing dinner. Food was semi warm and the rice was dry, use to be a good restaurant...quality of this restaurant is going down, very disappointed.
Delicious flavorful ethnic food. Service was awesome too.
I don't understand why this doesn't get more reviews and accolades. Hands down the best of Indian cuisine. My favorite Indian restaurant and a fantastic vegetarian offering.

Delicious authentic Indian food.  Highly recommend! I love that their food tastes fresh and unlike most Indian restaurants it isnt too oily or salty.  The inside of the restaurant is absolutely gorgeous with antique Indian decor.  I highly recommend the vegetarian or meat thali on the menu. You get a little bit of i beleive 6 or 7 menu items so it is similar to getting a buffet. I buy it for carryout a lot and it makes 3 to 4 meals for me.  Give it a try you will be glad!

I always get the palak (saag) paneer. It's fantastic here. Always have them bring the spice plate and garlic naan. Today had the Seekh kabob and the Fish Konkan Curry. Was very glad to have chosen both of those and would go back for everything I mentioned above, but the truth is that I haven't had anything here yet that I wouldn't eat. It's easily the best Indian cuisine in Bethesda
Nice restaurant but little bit costly but worth it

My favorite local Indian restaurant. The menu is divided into sections for each of India's major cuisines. You must get the Samosas. Mulligatawney soup is also a favorite. Most dishes are good to excellent including the various fish and lentil dishes. Ambiance is classy but not too stiff.

We really liked the food. Ordered samosa chat and fritters for starters and they were delicious. For main course we ordered kadai paneer and palak paneer with kulchas and naans. All of them tasted great. Kadai paneer was not on the menu but the bearer informed us when we were looking for paneer options. If you can update the menu it will be helpful for others.

Hadn't been here in a long time but will be back. It's a notch up from typical Indian, with four regional cuisines plus tandoor. Food was delicious, lots of variety, many veg choices. Prices are quite reasonable for Bethesda. Note latest reservation is 7:30.;
It was very nice restaurant! Quiet, artistic, and good lights. The food were excellent, pretty good portions, and very friendly servers! I had very good time with my husband for date night😃
An elegant restaurant with dishes from various regions of India.
Great Indian food. The showcase of food from different regions is really fun and unique. I enjoy the subtle differences.
Was there for lunch today. What I ordered was just ok.
Too Americanised for my liking. Goan fish curry was disaster. Saving grace rice kheer.
OMG... Really Nice
Whenever I come here, I get uncomfortably full because the food is so good that I don't want to stop eating. The decor is gorgeous and the staff is gracious as well. Always a wonderful experience!
Good food

Food was pretty good and did better than my expectation of other Indian restaurants I had visited in the past month. Really surprised how quite it was for how good the food is. Definitely worth mentioning and recommending to those who visit Bethesda.
Great Indian Food, great service and wonderful atmosphere... I think it is likely the best Indian food in Maryland
Exquisite fine Indian dining i absolutely love their Aloo gobi and their mango lassi.
Very good food and service. Selection is excellent  Tandoori chicken, garlic naan, and shrimp with curry and coconut sauce was terrific  highly recommend.
The food was okay but was not worth the hefty price tag.
Food was was really great, portions were decent and great atmosphere.
Great food.  Nice atmosphere.
Good

Beautiful ambience. Vegetarian Thali was average but Non vegetarian Thali was good. Prices are On the higher side. One time visit for me as there are better places with good food and reasonable pricing in the DMV area.
Great service and wonderful food!

This place is just outstanding. I have eaten at so many top shelf Indian restaurants and the food quality here is incredible. The Bhori Murghi is just wow. This is my third time here and I will be back
Exquisite flavors. Nice service.  5 stars.
Among the best Indian food we've had, with many vegan options.
Spice Xing,  another restaurant from the same group is far better..I was amazed how can two restaurants from same group differ that much..
My husband and I were walking by and saw this place, it was dinner time and we had an amazing meal. Simply amazing.
This was suggested to us by some Indian friends. We have been dining there ever since. Wonderful ambiance, and food.

Good food, good quality and reasonable portions. Friendly staff and fairly quick service, was there in a group of four on a Thursday night, restaurant was about half full so we were seated quickly. Will return again when in the area and hungry for Indian fare.
Clean, courteous staff
Best ambience and service. Loved the place.

Awful! Tikka Masala for $20 and they bring it in the most tiny container. The price & the  portion doesn't match at all. I can't believe this rip off!! They don't even serve 50% of what other restaurants serve you pay $20 and you're still starving! Wow!

Don't ask me why this place doesn't have five stars. I found it delicious! These guys not only have good food, they also have food from all regions of India- North, South, East, and West! If you don't think that matters, let me tell you something- the cuisines of India vary widely from region to region, as do languages, ethnicities, etc. Plenty of options for both carnivores and herbivores, with excellent sense of style and decor. Sure, its a bit pricey, but on the whole worth it! Only the Bombay Grill in St. Petersburg Florida comes close.
Very tasty. The chef's sampler was delicious.
Wonderful!!

I am writing as Kristen's daughter.  I am 11 years old, and I love Passage to India. My favorite menu item is Chicken Tikka Masala. I think this menu item is very good for other kids. The reason is, the curry is very mild, and the curry has a bit of a sweet and savory taste. It also tastes like an Indian-style tomato soup, with chicken in it, and it tastes delicious.
Great food and service, one of my favorite Bethesda restaurants.
Good food, good environment, great service.
Excellent!  Delicious cuisine and attentive staff. Try the Paneer Makhanee (sp?) ... it's possibly the best I've ever had! [usually no wait for lunch, but Saturday nights require a reservation.
Excellent service, great tasting food and a beautiful restaurant
Excellent food. A lot of choices from different parts of India not usually offered by other restaurants. Good service & delicious food. Will definitely go back. Highly recommended !!!
Loved this place. We have been to many, many Indian places and now the cuisine very well. This place was not disappointing.
Good food- good decor
Very good food and cozy atmosphere. We were a big party and accommodated pretty fast. Recommend.
Excellent food. Great service. Blend of cuisine from all the regions in India. Wine list is short but that's not a huge deal. Recommend trying kathal masala (jackfruit curry).
Amazing food, wonderful staff, best Indian in the DC region!!

Service was good. But the Paneer Anjeer Kofta was very sweet and Bhaigan Mirch ka Salan was very bland.I hope they incorporate some authentic Indian flavors in these dishes,instead of making it sweet and tasteless.
absolutely delicioso
Food is good, the lamb vindaloo was too spicy though
Great food

The food is delicious here.  I love Indian food and this place is one of our favorites.  The service is outstanding as well.  There are plenty of both vegan and meat dishes.  The rice comes beautifully on the plate, with cashews, cilantro or dried fruit on top...it is definitely a step up!!
The Chicken Tikka Masala and naan were amazing!

We went to eat lunch on Sunday as we heard good things about this restaurant but to our surprise food was tasteless and quantity was too less for the price one has to pay for maharaja brunch.  Paneer that we had was so tasteless and filled with sugar.  other things like dal makhani were served in sauce size container.  Naan was dry and no butter on it.  Our waiter was rushing us to get out of the restaurant. Although there were hardly anyone in the restaurant.  We are surprised they r still in business with such pathetic food and service.  Very disappointing.
Excellent experience !
Left after waiting over 15 minutes at table.

Food tasted good. Alcohol was stupendously expensive. Staff was all right. Clean facilities. If I did not have a Groupon, probably not worth it as the prices are sky high. Ambience though was good. The decor is authentic and tasteful.
Excellent.
Delicious goat and lamb dishes, naan was amazing, somosa was excellent.  Would come back.
Good food and good ambience

Lovely staff, beautiful amd airy decor, and deliscious food from a very descriptive menu with regional Indian traditional dishes. Naan bread was fresh and crusty, lamb was flavorful and tender, and the desserts were fantastic.
Nice idea to offer various Indian cuisines under one roof but execution needs more work.

I went here today with my wife and was blown away by the Salli Boli Jardaloo (lamb stew with apricot). This is the kind of food I'm into... flavors you that aren't easily come by. We are returning. 10/10 overall.
Excellent food and service. Substantial portions. Every dish is special.
Food not good

Overpriced low quality food. If you are seeking an authentic Indian taste, this is NOT the place for you. The server was extremely annoying to top it all, kept rushing us rudely to order the food. When he did come with our food, he dropped the plates with a thud carelessly.

This is probably the worst Indian restaurant I have been too.. and I have been to a ton of Indian restaurants along the east coast . The service was extremely poor.. the server was egging  us to order quickly ... when we asked us if he would like to recommend something ... he looked pretty disinterested and suggested some extremely common dishes . Food was pretty bland and this is coming from a person who doesn't like extremely spicy food. The restaurant was pretty expensive for their quality of food . I have had  better Indian food at 9 dollar buffets. My suggestion would to avoid this place.
Good food and good ambiance
Great sometimes then fair others
Love this place
Great food, and a generous, affordable lunch. They handle large groups well.
Excellent variety.
Delicious!
Good ambience and usual Indian food
Wonderful meal. Great service. Always a favorite.
Good food, nice ambiance.

The atmosphere was elegant and the lunch menu was reasonably priced.  Most of the selections were under $10.  I had the vegetable korma and my spouse has the shrimp curry.  The chai tea was smooth and delicious.  I wished we lived closer and we could visit more often.
Our Regular indian spot.  A little over price.
The enviroment is cosy and well decorated. But the food wasn't that exceptional, mild flAvor and garlic nan could hardly feel the garlic
An array of dishes coming from North, South, East and West India. They are willing to adjust a dish if you wish and are very patient and accomodating yo the customer.
Don't let the hipster neighborhood discourage you; this is the best Indian restaurant in the area.
Worst food ever.. papad is uncooked and stale..india palace is the best restaurant
It was fine..
Great Indian food. Especially desserts! Yummy. A bit pricy, though.
The decor was nice and interesting but the butter chicken was undercooked 2 times in a row and tasted horrible therefore I do not recommend it because of the reasons above
Good quality Indian food in a pretty indoor environment.  Staff was friendly and helpful.  Prices are slightly high for the food, but may be reasonable for Bethesda.
Good service, quick serving. Crowded but nice atmosphere. Affordable. Spicy lamb vindaloo!
The best

Local favorite of mine for Indian food. Somewhat of an upcaled place with the service to match and courses from each major region in India. The menu lets you know which options are vegan and the meals are plentiful. They're also open Christmas day.
Amazing, love the vegetarian platter
Food and service were great. Was packed on a week night.
For the price its ok.
great food, great service, great atmosphere equals wonderful experience!
Excellent food with a variety of options. I highly recommend it

We love this restaurant.  Extremely refined atmosphere.  Excellent food drawing from several of the distinctive regional cuisines of India and grouped accordingly.  The chef has always been very accommodating to any special requests.
username: Ellen & Barry Levy Real Estate Gurus

caption: Awesome ambience,  very efficient wait staff.  The food left a lot to be desired though. Bland and tasteless although it could just be out palates that are used to spicier food. Overall a decent experience but I probably won't go back.

I go there fairly often. Excelent Indian cuisine. Almost top level. More refined that Hande. Service is ok, but not yet great. Waiters are a bit brisk and stressed. Not for a calm dinner or lunch atmosphere, but still OK for a nice dinner.
Really good food but under average service.
The food was pretty good. The curry seafood was nice and spicy and the deserts were interesting. I couldn't say I've had anything that tasted like like before, but it was good.
The food was as good as any Indian that I have had.  Great selection and I loved that the menu was arranged according to area of India that the food originated.
Fantastic food. Royal service and food. Really glad we came here.

One of the very good places I have visited. The place is not that big and you might want to go early during peak times. The ambiance is very nice, with a Rajasthan kind of feel to it.  When I visited the place it was packed even though the service was good and timely. But the staff could do better with some informed suggestion on the dishes for first timers like me.  Finally, the most important thing, food was really good, didn't mind paying the extra bit of cash. Also the quantity is quite handful, between three healthy eaters, two subzi's and two breads (varied between naan's and stuffed cheese naan's) for each and three starters proved plentiful.
Got take-out here. Excellent Tikka Makhani and Goat curry. Excellent service.  Will definitely be coming back.
One of the more exotic places to eat indian food .. try the non-standard menu items and you will not feel let down !:)

Dumbed down Indian food that's essentially flavorless and bland. Samosas were good, but everything else was in tiny portions of bland slop that barely resembled the region of India from whence it came. Service was good, but doesn't make for a meal.
